<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/19438758-charming-frock"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1366013754i/19438758._UX100_CR0,29,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/19438758-charming-frock">Charming Frock</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I wondered if there was a problem with the 3rd book so I googled the names of the authors. Tucker Reed&apos;s full name is Aisling Tucker Moore-Reed and sh<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I wondered if there was a problem with the 3rd book so I googled the names of the authors. Tucker Reed's full name is Aisling Tucker Moore-Reed and she has had a hard go of it. She went to USC and became a "self-identified survivor of gendered violence." Both the college and LAPD dismissed the case so she published the man's name. Then SHE was disciplined for defaming her alleged attacker. I think she became a feminist activist in this cause. ANYWAY...Tucker moved back to Oregon after graduation. In 2018, Tucker shot and killed her maternal uncle. She plead to 2nd degree murder and is serving a 6 year sentence. As of January 2020, Reed faces new charges of supplying contraband and unlawfully possessing heroin in jail. There is more complete info in Wikipedia.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
